{"word":"ἀνία","slug":"ἀνία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνία</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> uncertain.\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>In <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b> and <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b> <el>ῑ</el>: in other Poets <el>ι</el> or <el>ῑ.</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>grief, sorrow, distress, trouble</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>actively, <el>δαιτὸς ἀνίη</el> <i>the bane</i> of our feast, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}